d-photography-109.jpg?resize=3D1500%2C1000&amp;ssl=3D1" alt=3D"Depth of fie=
ld in photography" class=3D"wp-image-253159"></span></figure></div>


<p>On the other hand, some images have very small zones of focus, which is =
known as <em><a aria-label=3D" (opens in a new tab)" href=3D"https://digita=
l-photography-school.com/how-to-get-shallow-depth-of-field-in-your-digital-=
photos/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener" class=3D"ek-link">sh=
allow depth of field</a></em>. A shallow DoF photo is generally immediately=
 recognizable because the subject will look tack-sharp while the background=
 is rendered as a <a aria-label=3D"smooth, creamy blur (opens in a new tab)=
" href=3D"https://digital-photography-school.com/how-to-achieve-nice-bokeh-=
in-plain-english/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener" class=3D"e=
k-link">smooth, creamy blur</a>:</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full"><span class=3D"responsive-image wp-=
image-211056" style=3D"width:1500px"><span class=3D"space" style=3D"width:1=
500px; padding-top:66.67%"></span><img data-recalc-dims=3D"1" loading=3D"la=
zy" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1500" height=3D"1000" src=3D"https://i0.wp.=
com/digital-photography-school.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/depth-of-fiel=
d-photography-45.jpg?resize=3D1500%2C1000&amp;ssl=3D1" alt=3D"Person in the=
 grass with a shallow depth of field effect" class=3D"wp-image-211056"></sp=
an></figure></div>


<p>This effect is especially popular in portraiture; photographers use it t=
o draw attention to their subject while preventing background distractions.=
 But you=E2=80=99ll also see shallow DoF macro photography, street photogra=
phy, photojournalism, and more.</p>



